A mass funeral service for the 21 young people who died in
the Enyobeni tavern in East London, will be held on Wednesday, 6 June. The teenagers 12 girls and nine boys mysteriously died
during a party organised at the Scenery Park venue on Sunday, 26 June. The mass funeral service will take place at Scenery Park
Sports Field, President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to be in attendance. The funeral company
AVBOB has pledged its support for each family’s funeral costs. The teenagers, aged between 13 and 17, forensic
investigations results on the cause of the deaths are still pending. Police reassured the families that they’d be informed when
the results were available. Police Minister Bheki Cele last week said a stampede had
been ruled out as the cause of death. The Eastern Cape Liquor Board has opened a criminal case
against the tavern owner, Siyakhangela Ndevu, and his wife, Vuyokazi, for allegedly
selling alcohol to underage children. Two kids were buried in East London yesterday, and today
another two kids will be also buried in East London separately.